				\begin{document}$$(I_{{\mathrm{exc}}})^p$$\end{document}, with p being the order of the process. For p = 1 this accounts to the regular linear absorption, while for p > 1 the process corresponds to a multiple photon absorption process via p−1 virtual states. Thus, by measuring the PL intensity in dependence of the excitation intensity and applying a power law fit, one can obtain the order of the process and thus determine the nature of the absorption.

The observation of resonances given by MEG in the MPE-PL of CsPbBr3 is realized when the following relation is fulfilled:1p×hν=N×Ex\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
